rComments: I just love her so much as a person, I learned A LOT in her class, not just academic stuff. It was eyes opening and I loved every second of it. Prof Bruckert is great. If you are looking to pass with little work then do not take her course. The online course was set up for students to succeed as long as they followed each class. Her mini assignments helped boost my grade up and were so helpful for the exams. She also gave the option of skipping the third exam. Lectures are fair in length.

The material for this class was super interesting which is why I didnt drop the class, but the course itself is very heavy (e.g.: 3 midterms, textbook, activity for every class, 12 page paper). Also, one of the TAs was more helpful then the other which became annoying. Overall, this class should be a 4th year class and not a 2nd year.

She uses modern, tangible material, and breaks down the course so that your strengths offset your weaknesses. I would highly suggest her as a seminar lecturer.

I'm not sure why Prof. Bruckert's ratings aren't higher. Genuinely enjoyed the class. She made sure to keep it relevant and introduce current events into our lectures. 2 really easy midterms and a final paper that requires no outside research. Definitely would take her again!

Christine is extremely passionate about her work. She teaches the material with great detail, is up to date with contemporary issues, and is always available through email.   You have to do the readings to pass, which is expected in university. The readings themselves are easy and enjoyable but make up a lot of the midterm and the final exam.

As I normally am a B+ A student , I was disappointed and had my lowest mark of 5 years University in this class, though I did the brunt of the work, Showed up for every class and did the assignments.
